Here is the Python code according to your specification:

```python
def prime_factors(numbers):
    num = numbers[1]
    factors = set()
    i = 2
    while i * i <= num:
        if num % i:
            i += 1
        else:
            num //= i
            factors.add(i)
    if num > 1:
        factors.add(num)
    return factors
```
Please note that the index is zero-based in Python. So, "integer at index 1" means the second integer in the list.
